OL,7,FBut the most recent research by the
OL,8,FNational Confidential Inquiry into
OL,9,FSuicide and Safety in Mental Health
OL,10,F(NCISH) shows 11% of people convicted
OL,11,Fof homicide in the UK were mental
OL,12,Fhealth patients - an average of 61
OL,13,Fconvictions a year.
OL,15,FStudies have found a key factor in
OL,16,Fthose cases is disengagement or
OL,17,Fsomeone not receiving the treatment
OL,18,Fthey need.
